What is WINRM ?

WinRM is  one component of windows hardware management feature that manages server hardware locally or remotely.

This feature includes a service that impthe WS_man , hardware diagnose and control through baseboard mangagement service (BMC) and a COM api and scripting objects that allows you to write applications that communicate remotely through the windows management or WS_MAN protocol.

Windows Remote Management or WinRM is microsoft implemetaTION OF WS-man protocol.

WinRM provides a secure ,efficient way for management applications to communicate with local or remote computers 

Winrm service is used for this .

When a server is connected to a BMC that support the WS_MAN standards, appliactions and scripts can use WinRM to communicate directly with BMC ,even when the operating system is offline .

What is WS amangement Protocol ?

Ws management protocol is a SOAP based firewall friendly protocol designed for systems to locate and exchange management information .

Port 5985 (HTTP) is used for domain joined system which are on same network 

Port 5986 (HTTPS) is used for domain joined system which are on different network .

WSman protocol is based on the following standard specification :

HTTPS

SOAP over http

soap 1.2

ws-addressing

ws-transfer
ws-enumeration
ws-eventing 

