What is MMC?

MMC is a windows utility which provides a unified interface to the System Admin and
advanced user to configure and manage system/computers.
MMC hosts administrative tools aka snap-ins to display different components of windows
settings.
MMC could also be utilised to manage and can configure remote computers using
WS-Management Protocol.
Q: What is the service name for MMC.
mmc.exe.

Snap-ins: MMC itself does not perform administrative functions; it acts as a container for snap-ins that do.

Customization: Users can create tailored consoles using mmc.exe and adding specific snap-ins through the File menu.

Remote Management: Snap-ins can be configured to manage other computers on a network.

Event forwarding 


-> WinRM supports event forwarding, allowing you to collect and forward events from remote
computers to a central location.
There are two types of event forwarding:
1. Collector initiated (Pull)
2. Source initiated (Push)


There are two types of event forwarding:

Collector Initiated Pull

Source Initiated Push

i) Collector Initiated Pull:

With the collector initiated subscription the collector will have to establish outbound WinRM connection & Pull events from the clients.

ii) Source Initiated Push:

With the source initiated subscription the collector will wait for incoming connection from the clients.

Common Requirements for Event forwarding:

A subscription has to be made on the collector server to forward events.

The WinRM has to be enabled on both client & server (collector server).

The WinRM service is already by default enabled in server but in client we have to enable it manually.

The account used to create the subscription need to have the permissions to read the event logs of the source computers. This permission can be configured using the built-in group called event log reader.

Requirement of collector initiated event forwarding:

The client has to reachable over the network & a firewall rule needs to be configured to adapt the incoming traffic.

The collector will have to contact each clients to pull the events for this reason this solution is not scalable & should not be preferred option.

Requirement of Source Initiated:

The collector has to reachable by the clients.

A policy has to be deployed to the client to point them to the collector.

